											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333; margin-bottom: 1em;">
											Dear %%FIRSTNAME%%,</p>

											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333;margin-bottom: 1em;">
												Every morning and evening, I am thankful for the mountains surrounding my Colorado home. To be quite honest, I can't imagine my life without them. </p>

											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333;margin-bottom: 1em;">
												I'm sure your life too would be much different without the things you love.</p>

											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333;margin-bottom: 1em;">
												Maybe that’s why you visited <a href="http://WhatIlove.org" style="border-bottom:1px dotted #487F00;font-weight:bold;color:#487F00;text-decoration:none;border-style: none;">WhatILove.org</a> to discover what's threatening the things you can’t live without ... and <a href="http://www.whatilove.org/#!/protect" style="border-bottom:1px dotted #487F00;font-weight:bold;color:#487F00;text-decoration:none;border-style: none;">how to protect them</a>.</p>

											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333;margin-bottom: 1em;">
												We noticed the natural world is very important to you. </p>

											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333;margin-bottom: 1em;">
												Whether you love the mountains' grandeur, like me, or the desert's dry heat or the cool touch of water on your toes, the wonder of nature is being affected by climate change.</p>

											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333;margin-bottom: 1em;">
												We noticed you love spending time in city streets.</p>

											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333;margin-bottom: 1em;">
												From San Francisco to New York City ... Cape Town to Tokyo ... or Sydney to London, the cities you may love to visit, or even live in are being affected by climate change. </p>

											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333;margin-bottom: 1em;">
												We noticed there are foods you just couldn't live without.</p>

											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333;margin-bottom: 1em;">
												Whether you’re a victim of the national bacon craze or constantly crave fresh fruits and vegetables, many of the foods you love are being affected by climate change.</p>

											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333;margin-bottom: 1em;">
												We noticed there are drinks you just couldn’t live without.
											</p>

											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333;margin-bottom: 1em;">
												Whether you're a wine connoisseur who orders for the table or you can't get your day started without a fresh cup of coffee (we've all been there), many of the drinks you love are being affected by climate change.
											</p>

											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333;margin-bottom: 1em;">
												No matter what you love, it's likely to be threatened by climate change. Increasing carbon levels in our atmosphere are leading to higher temperatures, longer heat waves, more frequent extreme weather events, and so much more. And they're changing life as we know it — possibly affecting the things you thought you couldn't live without.
											</p>

											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333;margin-bottom: 1em;">
												But the story doesn't end there. It's just where The Climate Reality Project comes in.We're making climate change the defining cultural issue of our time, and we want you to join us.
											</p>

											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333;margin-bottom: 1em;">
												Despite the near unanimous scientific consensus that man-made climate change is real and serious, anti-science skeptics funded by the fossil fuel industry keep denying reality in the media and confusing the public. But with What I Love, and many other initiatives, we're working together to share the truth about climate change and build real momentum for solutions. 
											</p>

											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333;margin-bottom: 1em;">
												And you've taken your first step towards helping us. <a href="http://www.whatilove.org/#!/learn" style="border-bottom:1px dotted #487F00;font-weight:bold;color:#487F00;text-decoration:none;border-style: none;">I hope you'll take the next step and learn how to protect the things you love</a>. 
											</p>
										
											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333;margin-bottom: 1em;">
												We all have something that's become part of us, something without which life would be fundamentally different. Even unimaginable. <a href="http://www.whatilove.org/#!/learn" style="border-bottom:1px dotted #487F00;font-weight:bold;color:#487F00;text-decoration:none;border-style: none;">Click here to learn how to protect what you love</a>. Then share it with a friend (or two).</p>

											<p style="font-family: Sans-Serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; padding: 5px; color:#333;margin-bottom: 1em;">  
